review:
This game still better than latest Sudden Strike and overwhelmingly better than Company of Heroes series.
Just think about it, it's 2014 and this game has: 
[list]
[*]majestic unit-level AI capable to sort outs things even without it's hand held; 
[*]impressive environment destruction system and even more impressive damage models for infantry and machines;
[*]great arrange of historically accurate units including heavy artillery ([b][i]really heavy[/i][/b] 355mm coastal batteries), tanks, light vehicles of all sorts and some aviation units;
[*]good variety of campaigns and missions, including stealth diversions\ambushes and wide-spread attacks;
[*]more or less usable game editor allowing you to modify existing or create new missions or even whole campaigns
[/list]

And look at this graphics! You still remember the game already spent it's 5 years, don't you?
I don't remember any single such a great WWII warfare game honestly.
I pray to see the next game of the series anytime.
